tinguished an Englishman from a Scot or a native Welshman on both sides of the border. The name may also have been acquired by English merchants who traded abroad or who lived and worked in a ‘French’ borough in England (one exclusively administered by Normans).","Irish: in Ireland, this name was used to denote an Englishman, often being adopted for Irish <b>Aingléis</b> ‘Englishman’ or through mistranslation for <b>Mac an Ghallóglaigh</b>, see   Gallogly   and   Golightly  ."]},{"name":"Gingles","meanings":["Irish: from the hybrid name <b>Mac Inglis</b> (Gaelic and English), meaning ‘son of the English speaker’, from Scottish   Inglis  . This surname is now rare in Britain and Ireland."]},{"name":"Inglish","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Inglis  .","English: variant of   English  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Inglis Murthuckstone was born in 1279, in Scotland, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Richard Scott 1st Of Rankilburn and Murthuckston."},"et":{"1279–":"1279–Surnud","1275–1320":"1275–1320","1310–1346":"1310–1346","1279–Female":"1279–Surnud","1346":"1346","1279":"1279","1310":"1310","1320":"1320","1275":"1275","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Rankilburn, Crosslee, Teviotdale, Scotland":"Crosslee, Renfrewshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1279–":"1279–Kuollut","1275–1320":"1275–1320","1310–1346":"1310–1346","1279–Female":"1279–Kuollut","1346":"1346","1279":"1279","1310":"1310","1320":"1320","1275":"1275","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Rankilburn, Crosslee, Teviotdale, Scotland":"Crosslee, Renfrewshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1279–":"1279–Décédée","1275–1320":"1275–1320","1310–1346":"1310–1346","1279–Female":"1279–Décédée","1346":"1346","1279":"1279","1310":"1310","1320":"1320","1275":"1275","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Écosse, Royaume-Uni","Rankilburn, Crosslee, Teviotdale, Scotland":"Crosslee, Renfrewshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Inglis Murthuckstone est née e